I have beat every class fairly easy in duels (rangers are tuff).<br>
so i wanted to try an SK. ok here is the basic scoop on me and the SK gear/levels.<br>
Me.<br>
60 dark elf Rogue<br>
mostly kael quest armor. RB main hand nightfall off hand<br>
1107 AC self buffed att.<br>
eye patch of plunder(haste).<br>
<br>
SK<br>
60 troll SK<br>
Dunno... toV quest, not sure for which faction though.<br>
Epic. <br>
can't remember haste item but he had a nice one.<br>
<br>
ok so anyway it kinda when't like this ( I don't parse logs or anything, wish i did)<br>
you have accepted duel blahblah.<br>
you pierce SK alot of times for alot of dmg ....<br>
SK laughs at your AC and doubles you for approx 220/245.( he hit me like this while I was behind him actually)<br>
you backstab SK for mediumly nice dmg.. SK at 75%<br>
you feel your lifeforce drain away whatever.. did 250 or so dmg lifetap.. then 180 lifetap right after. he could hit me no matter what direction he was facing.i resisted resisted all dots etc. ok im at about 50% health ... an &quot;You writh in the grip of agony. you have been hit for 1081 points of dmg.<br>
You have been slain by an overpowered bitch. at the end he had about 85% health and 70% mana also i used root/slow poison which he easily shadow steped out of an canceled (regained consentration from about 4-5 hits of 40-95).<br>
pretty pathetic... I have beaten every class fairly easily. yet SK tears me down no prob. anyone have any tactics against them? ;P<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhaunshar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khaunshar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/01 7:50:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK &gt; me .... bad</span><hr size=1> I play a SK, duel quite a bit.<br>
At lvl 57 I dueled a 60 rogue with full Mrylokar, epic and the Rapier of Orin I think, eyepatch .<br>
<br>
I killed him once easily, once barely.. why?<br>
1. Damage Shield. You hurt yourself quite a bit on the SKs, a 12 pt damage shield, plus maybe a Coldain 8 ring means PAIN.<br>
2. Lifetaps VERY hard to resist. You d have to sacrifice a lot of AC and probably Atk to get it up to the level where you MIGHT resist one. Basically, pure damage hardly interrupts hybrids, high channeling and high AC.<br>
3. In PvP, you can attack anyone in melee range, no matter if he is behind, in front of or at your side. Backstab still is back only. that means once you step into reach, unless you can time it very well or he has no haste, you ll eat these heavy hits. The SK epic is a superb dueling weapon, it almost seems like it was made for that purpose.<br>
4. Harm Touch : From 55 on a nobrainer, except on healers you just hammer it, and they go down by 2 or 3 bubs.<br>
5. Dots and Pet do not matter too much.<br>
<br>
All in all I am surprised that poison worked (self only DMF like spell, 40 or 50 PR), and I think its extremely hard for a pure melee class to beat a Shadow Knight in a duel situation. Shadow Step, damage shield and lifetaps just mean he ll live on forever, and these heavy hitting swords mean high damage, and little point in riposte discs, as well as dangerously high riposte damage from him.<br>
<br>
I d say you cannot beat him most of the time if he knows his stuff.<br>
<br>
