<br>
About lifetaps: I know a druid who claimed he resisted roughly half of the lifetaps in a duel with 177 MR.<br>
<br>
 <p>@~}~~   Khaunshar T'Varith   ~~{~@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/01 9:47:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK &gt; me .... bad</span><hr size=1> Did you use any disciplines? <p><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/bscreamspvp"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/sig/joyous.gif"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhaiyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhaiyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 4:17:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK &gt; me .... bad</span><hr size=1> your gonna laugh... but i didnt even get the chance to use one..../sigh he just did too much unresistable dmg too fast..<br>
he got a lucky 245/230 or so melee hit (while i was behind him ! grr!)then a 270 lifetap and a 170 lifetap then another 170 lfetap(these are while im hitting him etc. then HT for exsactly 1020 dmg. I just don't understand how he could channel through my hits like that. next thing you know they are gonna give HT a lifetap effect (see casters realm balancing issues for SK... they are asking for it lol) oh well. I'll find a tactic im sure thanks for the help <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhaunshar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khaunshar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 4:44:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK &gt; me .... bad</span><hr size=1> The problem with Harm Touch balancing is (which is why the some SKs asked for the lifetap version) that it has really limited use in PvE situations. Additionally, SKs lack the tanking ability to fulfill their role as a tank on raids, and the community has been looking for various ways to improve SKs uber mob tanking without using a disc like defensive. Lifetap HT was one of the rather odd (IMO) requests, and obviously wasnt done with PvP in mind.<br>
<br>
Btw, the upgrade of HT to be almost unresistable has actually been a nerf for all classes including SKs, since mobs now have a sooo much better HT <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
