Anyway, as I said, dont hope to interrupt a high AC caster (read: Paladin, Hybrid, very well equipped cleric) with pure damage, it will not work. I successfully channel through quad rounds of 380 hits on a fairly constant basis.<br>
<br>
 <p>@~}~~   Khaunshar T'Varith   ~~{~@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/01 6:17:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK &gt; me .... bad</span><hr size=1> Shadow knights are very hard to deal with.  You can cope with them, but you're going to have problems - especially with life leach and harmtouch.<br>
